00:19:09.420 --> 00:19:12.339
So, please, if you did not get your question asked here,

00:19:12.339 --> 00:19:15.500
find Garrick, I'm sure he'll be around the hall, available.

00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:18.459
But, other than brand.yaml, what is your favorite trick

00:19:18.459 --> 00:19:22.099
to not make Shiny apps look like a 2019 Shiny app?

00:19:22.099 --> 00:19:25.020
Yeah, my favorite trick is to use BSLib.

00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:27.479
So, or Shiny for Python.

00:19:27.479 --> 00:19:29.859
But, yeah, BSLib is where all of the new,

00:19:29.859 --> 00:19:31.780
fun stuff is happening for Shiny.

00:19:31.780 --> 00:19:35.900
And automatically, just by using some functions from BSLib,

00:19:35.900 --> 00:19:38.859
you just get nicer looking apps out of the box.

00:19:38.859 --> 00:19:40.859
So, BSLib and brand.yaml together,

00:19:40.859 --> 00:19:43.939
